1
00:00:01,110 --> 00:00:03,710
(Episode 55)

2
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:07,280
- Hey, you!
- My goodness. What is this?

3
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:08,850
Darn you...

4
00:00:08,850 --> 00:00:10,620
- What is this?
- It was you, wasn't it?

5
00:00:10,750 --> 00:00:14,020
In broad daylight,
you lured my husband to this dump?

6
00:00:14,090 --> 00:00:15,950
- That's not true.
- Get away from me!

7
00:00:15,950 --> 00:00:17,560
No, you've got the wrong person!

8
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:19,320
- Get away!
- Let go of me.

9
00:00:20,060 --> 00:00:21,860
What do you mean "wrong person?"

10
00:00:21,860 --> 00:00:24,630
They say you've been a faithful widow
for 30 years?

11
00:00:24,860 --> 00:00:27,930
So you must've been desperate
all those long, lonely nights, right?

12
00:00:27,970 --> 00:00:30,800
Is that why you lure any man you find
to this hotel?

13
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:31,900
What did you just say?

14
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:34,370
Do you have any idea who I am?

15
00:00:34,370 --> 00:00:35,470
What did you say?

16
00:00:35,770 --> 00:00:39,710
You have the nerve to run your mouth
after seducing my husband.

17
00:00:39,880 --> 00:00:42,810
This is so absurd I'm speechless.
Listen here.

18
00:00:42,810 --> 00:00:44,220
Do you even know where you are?

19
00:00:44,550 --> 00:00:45,880
Why are you just standing there?

20
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:47,220
Get this woman out of here, now!

21
00:00:47,390 --> 00:00:49,850
Why, you... Darn it.

22
00:00:51,690 --> 00:00:52,760
You lunatic...

23
00:00:53,930 --> 00:00:55,990
- You can't act like this here.
- A tramp like you...

24
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:57,900
Unbelievable.

25
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:00,170
Here, take this!

26
00:01:00,270 --> 00:01:01,570
Here, take this!

27
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:03,370
Take this!

28
00:01:09,170 --> 00:01:10,180
Let me go. Hey, you homewrecker!

29
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:20,490
Security!

30
00:01:21,090 --> 00:01:23,760
Don't you dare break another woman's
heart. Got it?

31
00:01:24,090 --> 00:01:27,390
If you make her cry,
you'll cry tears of blood.

32
00:01:27,460 --> 00:01:28,560
You little!

33
00:01:29,390 --> 00:01:30,500
Gosh, darn it.

34
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Gosh.

35
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:34,300
Gosh! Get off me!

36
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:38,440
- Darn it!
- Get that woman! Get her! That one!

37
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,170
Hurry! Get her!

38
00:01:41,910 --> 00:01:46,380
Mom, what in the world happened?
Gosh, what's that sour smell?

39
00:01:47,180 --> 00:01:48,180
Gosh.

40
00:01:51,220 --> 00:01:52,450
That absolute lunatic!

41
00:01:53,380 --> 00:01:55,950
Gosh, what is all this? That crazy woman!

42
00:01:58,290 --> 00:02:00,190
Gosh, seriously!

43
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:04,600
What?

44
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:06,300
Where'd she go?

45
00:02:09,570 --> 00:02:11,670
Where did she put the approval documents?

46
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:15,440
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

47
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:27,250
(See you at the Dream Hotel coffee shop
at 2:00 p.m. From Your Love)

48
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,960
Gosh, that's enough. You can go.

49
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:41,370
Please take good care of my mom
so she doesn't catch a cold.

50
00:02:45,140 --> 00:02:46,140
This way.

51
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:47,640
Gosh, I feel dizzy.

52
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,240
Go on, Mom.

53
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:00,550
So, how'd I do?

54
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:04,660
Ma'am, you were incredible.
And your grip is still as strong as ever.

55
00:03:04,790 --> 00:03:06,860
You say that as if you've had
your hair pulled by me before.

56
00:03:08,590 --> 00:03:10,500
Anyway, thank you.

57
00:03:11,330 --> 00:03:14,100
But have we met somewhere before?

58
00:03:14,900 --> 00:03:17,940
I doubt it. Where would I have ever
seen you, ma'am?

59
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:22,640
I heard you were well-known
at the market, so I hired you.

60
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:27,310
Is that right? Well, thank you anyway.

61
00:03:28,510 --> 00:03:32,220
Business was slow, debts were piling up,
and I really needed some quick cash.

62
00:03:33,420 --> 00:03:34,420
One moment.

63
00:03:35,420 --> 00:03:36,420
You know what to do, right?

64
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:43,430
Oh my!

65
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:47,430
This is a thick envelope.
I take it this means "zip it."

66
00:03:47,730 --> 00:03:51,640
Don't you worry.
Because I'm nothing if not loyal.

67
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:53,810
Thanks!

68
00:04:06,650 --> 00:04:07,650
Chae Hwa Young,

69
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:12,020
you're in for some more humiliation.
It'd be a shame if this is where it ends.

70
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,640
When we find who's behind this,
they won't get away with it.

71
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:29,340
Find that woman.
Find her and drag her to me at once.

72
00:04:30,010 --> 00:04:31,510
For obstruction of business
and public humiliation,

73
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:33,680
sue her for everything we possibly can.

74
00:04:34,210 --> 00:04:35,210
Yes, ma'am.

75
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:38,550
Mom, you have to see this.

76
00:04:39,150 --> 00:04:41,850
- Mom, what are we going to do?
- What is it now?

77
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:45,320
- A video of you is all over the internet.
- What?

78
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:50,260
(CEO Chae at Her Own Hotel
Today's "Makgeolli Woman!")

79
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,130
Unbelievable!

80
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:57,500
Ma'am.

81
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:01,040
Get this taken down! Right now!

82
00:05:03,340 --> 00:05:06,540
I'll threaten the blogger and make them
take this post down right now.

83
00:05:07,850 --> 00:05:11,680
- But Mom, this is actually hilarious.
- Ma Seo Rin.

84
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:14,850
Your mother was just humiliated,
and you think it's hilarious?

85
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:18,590
No, I mean the picture is hilarious. Look.

86
00:05:18,660 --> 00:05:20,990
It says you're taking a makgeolli bath.

87
00:05:22,690 --> 00:05:23,930
The "Nation's Homewrecker?"

88
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:27,630
Mom, this is just a huge misunderstanding,
right?

89
00:05:27,930 --> 00:05:30,570
- That woman just misunderstood, right?
- Of course she did.

90
00:05:31,170 --> 00:05:33,570
Deal with this before it spreads further.
Immediately!

91
00:05:33,670 --> 00:05:35,210
Okay, okay, I get it.

92
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,550
What is this?

93
00:05:44,550 --> 00:05:45,580
(See you at the Dream Hotel coffee shop
at 2:00 p.m. From Your Love)

94
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:46,580
What?

95
00:05:48,020 --> 00:05:49,790
Wait, how did you get this?

96
00:05:51,890 --> 00:05:53,730
Were you planning to meet Professor Kang?

97
00:05:54,290 --> 00:05:57,060
So you went to that coffee shop
and ended up getting humiliated.

98
00:05:57,660 --> 00:05:59,500
How can we press charges against
that woman...

99
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:00,800
under these circumstances?

100
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:01,900
Manager Lee.

101
00:06:02,230 --> 00:06:03,870
So you're telling me
to just look the other way?

102
00:06:04,470 --> 00:06:06,540
You expect me
to just take the humiliation?

103
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:07,910
Is that it?

104
00:06:09,810 --> 00:06:13,540
- I won't. I'm going to kill that woman.
- Break up with Professor Kang. Right now.

105
00:06:14,810 --> 00:06:15,810
Only then can I...

106
00:06:16,910 --> 00:06:18,220
take care of this mess.

107
00:06:19,450 --> 00:06:22,950
Manager Lee. Lee Kang Hyuk!
Get back in here right now!

108
00:06:23,490 --> 00:06:24,760
Hey!

109
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:29,490
I'm going to make them all pay!

110
00:06:34,370 --> 00:06:35,900
I can't take this anymore!

111
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,770
Why is she making such a big deal
about a little humiliation?

112
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:40,970
This is only the beginning,
Chae Hwa Young.

113
00:06:41,710 --> 00:06:44,480
I'm going to make you suffer so much
that death will seem like a relief.

114
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:46,080
Just you wait.

115
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:50,850
I never should have gone
to meet Professor Kang.

116
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:53,850
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

117
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:11,200
Hello, Hwa Young.

118
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:15,010
Professor, how could you send me
a note like that?

119
00:07:15,070 --> 00:07:18,580
- Wait, a note? From me?
- I went to the coffee shop to meet you,

120
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:21,650
and some awful woman got the wrong idea,
grabbed my hair,

121
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:23,920
and even had makgeolli dumped all over me.

122
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:27,720
It was so humiliating!
How am I supposed to live this down?

123
00:07:27,790 --> 00:07:31,460
Wait, Hwa Young, please calm down.
What are you talking about?

124
00:07:31,690 --> 00:07:36,060
Pardon? You went to that shop to meet me?
I never arranged anything like that.

125
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:38,730
But you left a note for me in my office.

126
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:41,100
You came by yesterday.
Why would you come again...

127
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:44,140
No, I'm just on my way home
from the university right now.

128
00:07:44,340 --> 00:07:46,970
I haven't even had time
to stop by the Dream Hotel.

129
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:50,740
And if I'd seen you
getting attacked like that,

130
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:53,780
do you really think I would have
just stood by and watched?

131
00:07:55,250 --> 00:07:57,220
Hwa Young, are you okay? Are you hurt?

132
00:08:00,590 --> 00:08:01,590
Director Ma.

133
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:04,060
What are you doing here?

134
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:07,490
The CEO is inside, right?

135
00:08:09,790 --> 00:08:10,800
Okay, I get it.

136
00:08:11,730 --> 00:08:12,930
I'll call you back.

137
00:08:17,370 --> 00:08:18,370
Wait a minute.

138
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,870
If Professor Kang didn't send it,

139
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:23,840
then who on earth could have done this?

140
00:08:30,310 --> 00:08:33,320
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

141
00:08:36,190 --> 00:08:39,290
What? What's that yeasty smell?

142
00:08:41,790 --> 00:08:44,660
It's nothing, General Manager Kang.

143
00:08:45,330 --> 00:08:46,600
I wonder if it still smells.

144
00:08:47,130 --> 00:08:51,170
Seo Rin, keep General Manager Kang company
while I go wash up.

145
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:53,270
Okay, got it. Hurry back.

146
00:08:53,740 --> 00:08:55,740
You smell like you fell
into a vat of booze.

147
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,540
It's not what it looks like.

148
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,240
Please don't get the wrong idea.

149
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:11,420
What happened to the CEO?

150
00:09:12,090 --> 00:09:13,090
I'm not really sure.

151
00:09:14,660 --> 00:09:16,090
Anyway, I'm a bit busy.

152
00:09:16,630 --> 00:09:18,760
Do you really have amnesia?

153
00:09:19,660 --> 00:09:21,130
You don't remember who I am either?

154
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:24,000
Am I supposed to?

155
00:09:24,900 --> 00:09:26,970
No, but...

156
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,540
I should get going then.

157
00:09:33,810 --> 00:09:34,810
What was that about?

158
00:09:35,410 --> 00:09:37,750
She used to follow me around
so relentlessly.

159
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,990
And now she's being weirdly polite.

160
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:43,290
This is weird.

161
00:09:47,390 --> 00:09:48,790
What if...

162
00:09:49,290 --> 00:09:51,860
Chef Kang Jun Ho figures out
I'm not Seo Rin?

163
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,170
Before anyone else finds out,

164
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:57,130
I need to hurry and find proof
that Chae Hwa Young killed my dad.

165
00:10:12,580 --> 00:10:13,650
Baek Ho.

166
00:10:15,820 --> 00:10:20,020
Hello, ma'am. Can I ask you
a quick question?

167
00:10:20,020 --> 00:10:21,130
Sure.

168
00:10:21,130 --> 00:10:24,660
Did you see a lunch box left around here
about a month ago?

169
00:10:25,130 --> 00:10:26,430
A lunch box?

170
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:28,930
Yes, it was a lunch box
from a side dish shop,

171
00:10:28,930 --> 00:10:30,430
and we heard it was so delicious,

172
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,200
we were wondering
if you knew anything about it.

173
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,740
Something delicious, you say...

174
00:10:35,740 --> 00:10:39,980
You mean the one left behind a pillar
in the executive parking lot?

175
00:10:40,610 --> 00:10:42,180
Yes! Did you try it?

176
00:10:42,380 --> 00:10:46,850
A cleaner, Mrs. Kim, brought it over.
She didn't know who it belonged to.

177
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:51,690
So we all shared it. And let me tell you,
it was to die for.

178
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:53,920
So it was in the executive parking lot?

179
00:10:54,030 --> 00:10:56,430
Yes, behind a pillar
in the executive parking lot.

180
00:10:56,860 --> 00:10:58,830
The executive parking lot is on B3.

181
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:01,570
And you don't happen to know
where the lunch box came from?

182
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:04,100
That's the lunch box Dad brought.

183
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:07,000
That has to be Dad's lunch box.

184
00:11:08,010 --> 00:11:11,580
Should we ask CEO Chae to show us the CCTV
from the executive parking lot?

185
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:19,580
It's our Seo Rin's first day at work,

186
00:11:19,650 --> 00:11:21,790
I wonder if she's doing okay.

187
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:24,960
Honey, don't waste your time worrying.

188
00:11:25,190 --> 00:11:27,360
Since when has Seo Rin
ever taken her job seriously?

189
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:29,760
What?

190
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:33,500
I mean... That's just how she is.

191
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:37,000
She's probably just goofing off,
so don't worry.

192
00:11:47,650 --> 00:11:49,410
(Yang Mal Ja)

193
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:52,750
Ms. Yang Mal Ja?

194
00:11:53,820 --> 00:11:54,820
Yes?

195
00:11:56,420 --> 00:11:58,420
That lunch box in
the executive parking lot the other day...

196
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:00,260
You said you all shared it, right?

197
00:12:01,290 --> 00:12:02,330
Yes.

198
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,700
Fire the cleaner, Yang Mal Ja.

199
00:12:14,110 --> 00:12:15,370
What? Why?

200
00:12:17,370 --> 00:12:18,480
Do you need a reason?

201
00:12:19,510 --> 00:12:20,910
No, sir. I understand.

202
00:12:29,350 --> 00:12:30,390
Yes, CEO.

203
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:33,720
As I told you, the CCTV footage
from the executive parking lot...

204
00:12:33,790 --> 00:12:35,730
has been completely wiped.
There's not a trace left.

205
00:12:36,690 --> 00:12:38,500
Also, I've already taken care
of that cleaner.

206
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:41,130
You won't be hearing about this again.

207
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:44,270
Okay, got it.

208
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:49,270
Since the CCTV footage is
from a while ago,

209
00:12:49,770 --> 00:12:51,940
they say it'll take some time
to review it.

210
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:54,910
But I'll personally make sure
to look into it for you.

211
00:12:55,180 --> 00:12:57,750
- We're counting on you.
- Don't worry about a thing.

212
00:12:58,180 --> 00:12:59,220
By the way,

213
00:13:00,350 --> 00:13:01,620
I've been seeing you a lot lately.

214
00:13:02,390 --> 00:13:05,290
I thought I told you
I'm a very busy woman.

215
00:13:06,490 --> 00:13:07,490
It's just that...

216
00:13:08,030 --> 00:13:09,090
I'm sorry.

217
00:13:16,230 --> 00:13:17,570
I'll have to start coming here more often.

218
00:13:18,140 --> 00:13:20,600
The vegetables are so fresh
and the variety is great. I love it.

219
00:13:20,870 --> 00:13:22,140
This would be a great spot
for company dinners.

220
00:13:22,570 --> 00:13:25,040
Thank you, sir. Please come again.

221
00:13:25,110 --> 00:13:28,210
- Of course. Hope business is good!
- Goodbye.

222
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:35,550
Tae Pyung, did you find anything out?

223
00:13:36,050 --> 00:13:37,760
Who Jang Mi came here to meet.

224
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:41,060
That. I still haven't figured that out.

225
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:45,830
Do you know any of Jang Mi's friends
by name?

226
00:13:46,060 --> 00:13:47,200
Jang Mi's friends?

227
00:13:48,130 --> 00:13:49,130
I don't know.

228
00:13:49,900 --> 00:13:54,170
Between work and taking care of her mom,
she never really had time to see friends.

229
00:13:54,670 --> 00:13:55,670
That's true.

230
00:13:57,470 --> 00:13:58,640
Poor Jang Mi.

231
00:13:59,510 --> 00:14:00,540
Okay.

232
00:14:03,310 --> 00:14:04,580
It's Ok Hee and Tok Hee.

233
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:07,790
Grandma, you drew some pretty princesses.

234
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:12,660
Ok Hee and Tok Hee are
Suk Hee's daughters. Princesses.

235
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:13,860
What's this, Mom?

236
00:14:14,290 --> 00:14:17,560
Did you draw Jang Mi and Tae Sook too?
You made her look so pretty.

237
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:18,860
What's gotten into you?

238
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:22,000
Silly Tae Pyung.
I drew Ok Hee and Tok Hee.

239
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:23,570
Right.

240
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:25,270
So you drew Jang Mi.

241
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,500
I get it.

242
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:31,340
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

243
00:14:33,210 --> 00:14:36,350
In broad daylight,
you lured my husband to this dump?

244
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:39,150
- That's not true.
- Get away from me!

245
00:14:39,150 --> 00:14:40,650
Let go of me.

246
00:14:40,850 --> 00:14:42,820
What do you mean "wrong person?"

247
00:14:42,820 --> 00:14:45,720
They say you've been a faithful widow
for 30 years?

248
00:14:45,860 --> 00:14:49,160
So you must've been desperate
all those long, lonely nights, right?

249
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:52,100
Is that why you lure any man you find
to this hotel?

250
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:56,370
That crazy woman wasn't mistaking me
for someone else.

251
00:14:57,070 --> 00:14:58,670
She was targeting me.

252
00:15:01,410 --> 00:15:03,410
If Professor Kang wasn't the one
who left the note,

253
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:05,340
then who was it?

254
00:15:08,450 --> 00:15:11,220
Get me a list of everyone
who entered my office today.

255
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:13,420
I want the exact times,
down to the minute.

256
00:15:20,020 --> 00:15:22,490
Jang Mi, I'm right here.

257
00:15:23,230 --> 00:15:24,400
You can hear my voice, right?

258
00:15:25,130 --> 00:15:28,630
We caught the person who did this to you
and got a confession, but...

259
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,670
for some reason,
just like with my father's case...

260
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,340
something doesn't add up.

261
00:15:34,470 --> 00:15:37,710
I know for a fact someone else was injured
in the accident with you...

262
00:15:38,310 --> 00:15:39,410
and it's just strange.

263
00:15:41,210 --> 00:15:42,210
Jang Mi.

264
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:43,880
Please, just tell me.

265
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:46,850
Who did you meet
on the day of the accident?

266
00:15:47,650 --> 00:15:50,150
Why were you in so much pain
at the Han River?

267
00:15:56,490 --> 00:15:59,430
Today's meeting is to go over
Dream Resort's Food and Beverage...

268
00:15:59,630 --> 00:16:01,730
and finalize the initial working concept.

269
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:05,570
For the Food and Beverage side,
our concept for the resort...

270
00:16:05,640 --> 00:16:07,770
is "local premium."

271
00:16:07,770 --> 00:16:10,310
Using local produce
and seasonal ingredients,

272
00:16:10,310 --> 00:16:13,540
we'll feature fine dining
and a casual market-style...

273
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:15,310
food and beverage space.

274
00:16:15,710 --> 00:16:17,310
We're especially planning...

275
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:20,480
a farm-to-table chef's table
as a core feature.

276
00:16:21,990 --> 00:16:24,290
I don't understand a single word
they're saying.

277
00:16:26,290 --> 00:16:28,290
(Executive Director Kang Jun Ho)

278
00:16:31,660 --> 00:16:32,730
Director Ma.

279
00:16:33,830 --> 00:16:36,430
I'm getting you alone
with General Manager Kang,

280
00:16:36,430 --> 00:16:39,540
so when your memory comes back,
don't forget you owe me one.

281
00:16:41,870 --> 00:16:42,910
General Manager Kang.

282
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:46,410
I've been called back to the main office,
so I'll be heading out first.

283
00:16:46,710 --> 00:16:50,450
You two can continue the discussion.
I'll rejoin you tomorrow.

284
00:16:50,510 --> 00:16:54,250
All right. If you have to go
to the main office, it can't be helped.

285
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:03,430
Director Ma.

286
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,930
What Team Leader Jin and I
were just discussing,

287
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:09,570
did you understand any of it?

288
00:17:11,340 --> 00:17:13,770
Of course. What do you take me for?

289
00:17:14,770 --> 00:17:16,770
Then, based on the initial investment,

290
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:18,980
you should be able to analyze
the rate of return as well.

291
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:27,650
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

292
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:28,720
You can go now.

293
00:17:33,860 --> 00:17:35,960
Who was the person
who stopped by before two?

294
00:17:36,460 --> 00:17:37,560
Who was it?

295
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:40,260
(1:10 p.m., Director Ma Seo Rin)

296
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,200
Seo Rin?

297
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:46,340
Seo Rin was here at that time?

298
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:00,150
Thank goodness.

299
00:18:00,780 --> 00:18:03,490
Since this one has the mole,
she must be my Seo Rin.

300
00:18:06,190 --> 00:18:07,830
I confirmed it myself.

301
00:18:08,490 --> 00:18:11,600
It is Seo Rin.
There's no way it's Oh Jang Mi.

302
00:18:11,660 --> 00:18:12,960
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

303
00:18:14,730 --> 00:18:15,770
But what if...

304
00:18:17,170 --> 00:18:19,070
Seo Rin is actually Oh Jang Mi?

305
00:18:25,910 --> 00:18:27,910
Why are you looking at me like that?

306
00:18:28,580 --> 00:18:29,910
I just can't believe it.

307
00:18:30,350 --> 00:18:34,120
I can't believe it either.
To think I'm face-to-face...

308
00:18:34,650 --> 00:18:36,350
with my idol, Chef Kang Jun Ho.

309
00:18:37,490 --> 00:18:38,990
Does amnesia...

310
00:18:40,790 --> 00:18:42,890
really turn someone into
such a gentle lamb?

311
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:47,130
Shouldn't you keep things professional?

312
00:18:47,130 --> 00:18:48,830
Aren't we in the middle of work right now?

313
00:18:50,330 --> 00:18:51,370
I guess we are.

314
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:53,500
We're supposed to be working,

315
00:18:54,510 --> 00:18:56,370
but I can't seem to take my eyes off you.

316
00:18:56,740 --> 00:18:58,880
- That's funny.
- What are you talking about?

317
00:18:59,340 --> 00:19:00,640
Are you saying I'm a joke?

318
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:03,480
This is unbelievable.

319
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:10,490
I asked you a question.

320
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:12,620
Why aren't you answering me?

321
00:19:14,730 --> 00:19:18,560
I asked if you can analyze the ROI
on our initial investment.

322
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:21,900
Well, I...

323
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:27,070
As you know, my memory is still a bit hazy
from the accident.

324
00:19:29,940 --> 00:19:33,110
I always wanted to meet you
in the kitchen, Chef Kang Jun Ho,

325
00:19:33,510 --> 00:19:38,380
but not like this.
Chef, please, give me a break this once.

326
00:19:38,820 --> 00:19:42,420
If you don't know, just say so.
You never knew to begin with.

327
00:19:42,690 --> 00:19:46,420
And don't even think about using amnesia
as a convenient excuse.

328
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:48,390
After all, you only came to the office...

329
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:50,860
to keep up appearances anyway.

330
00:19:53,060 --> 00:19:55,800
Don't you think you're being too harsh
just because I have amnesia?

331
00:19:55,970 --> 00:19:59,170
As the Director of Food and Beverage,
you should know those figures by heart.

332
00:19:59,770 --> 00:20:01,000
If you really have amnesia,

333
00:20:01,410 --> 00:20:04,110
you should have studied up
before coming into this meeting.

334
00:20:07,340 --> 00:20:08,750
Excuse me, I need to use the restroom.

335
00:20:10,310 --> 00:20:11,420
Suit yourself.

336
00:20:20,660 --> 00:20:23,760
Oh Jang Mi. You have to be Ma Seo Rin.

337
00:20:24,660 --> 00:20:26,100
You can't let this shake you.

338
00:20:33,970 --> 00:20:36,610
Oh no, did the mole already rub off?

339
00:20:38,510 --> 00:20:41,910
Chae Hwa Young won't push my hair aside
to check, will she?

340
00:20:47,380 --> 00:20:48,390
But what if...

341
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:51,660
What if Chae Hwa Young goes to check
on the real Seo Rin?

342
00:20:55,590 --> 00:20:57,860
It turns out Professor Kang
never came to my office.

343
00:20:58,500 --> 00:21:00,660
According to the message, before two,

344
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:03,530
the one going in and out of my office
is the culprit.

345
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:06,170
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

346
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:07,300
Take a look at this.

347
00:21:08,140 --> 00:21:09,510
The only person was my Seo Rin.

348
00:21:10,570 --> 00:21:11,680
That can't be right.

349
00:21:12,510 --> 00:21:15,850
Why would Seo Rin leave a note
like that here?

350
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:19,120
But what if...

351
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:22,390
it wasn't Seo Rin,
but her twin, Oh Jang Mi?

352
00:21:23,850 --> 00:21:24,860
You don't think...

353
00:21:26,020 --> 00:21:30,060
I didn't check Oh Jang Mi's ear in the ER.
That's what's bothering me.

354
00:21:30,130 --> 00:21:32,660
But you confirmed the mole
on Seo Rin's ear.

355
00:21:33,730 --> 00:21:34,900
That's true, but...

356
00:21:35,530 --> 00:21:38,470
What if I was mistaken? No,

357
00:21:39,570 --> 00:21:42,570
what if it was just a speck of blood
that splattered on her,

358
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:45,110
and I mistook it for a mole?

359
00:21:47,110 --> 00:21:50,580
Manager Lee, I need to go to
Oh Jang Mi's room and see for myself.

360
00:21:51,110 --> 00:21:53,320
Yes, ma'am.
I'll have the car brought around.

361
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:07,200
I thought you were home for the day.

362
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:09,700
Where are you off to this late?

363
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:14,470
Why? Worried your wife is going to
have an affair?

364
00:22:15,070 --> 00:22:16,810
Good grief, honey.

365
00:22:17,470 --> 00:22:20,540
Don't worry.
I'm going to get our Baek Ho married off.

366
00:22:20,710 --> 00:22:22,050
What are you talking about?

367
00:22:22,510 --> 00:22:25,920
There's a young woman
who's head over heels for our Baek Ho.

368
00:22:26,450 --> 00:22:27,450
A young woman?

369
00:22:27,850 --> 00:22:30,590
Team Leader Jin Hong Ju from Dream Hotel.

370
00:22:30,890 --> 00:22:33,320
Team Leader Jin?

371
00:22:35,890 --> 00:22:36,890
She'd be a good match, don't you think?

372
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:41,930
I approve of her as a match for Baek Ho.

373
00:22:42,500 --> 00:22:45,800
I can't stand to watch him
so hung up on Oh Jang Mi.

374
00:22:46,970 --> 00:22:48,970
My son is what's most important to me.

375
00:22:49,210 --> 00:22:51,580
But it's Baek Ho's feelings that matter.

376
00:22:52,140 --> 00:22:54,980
Do you really think he has eyes
for anyone else right now?

377
00:22:55,550 --> 00:23:00,080
- You think so?
- Plus, Baek Ho is a pure-hearted kid.

378
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:05,190
He's not one to look out for himself.
He loves unconditionally.

379
00:23:06,260 --> 00:23:10,260
It's true our Baek Ho
is a hopeless romantic.

380
00:23:11,290 --> 00:23:15,270
He's just like you in that way.
It's uncanny.

381
00:23:24,670 --> 00:23:25,680
Baek Ho.

382
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:29,410
You didn't forget you were treating me
to dinner, did you?

383
00:23:30,410 --> 00:23:32,920
Come on, son. Let me enjoy a dinner
paid for by my boy.

384
00:23:37,450 --> 00:23:39,660
Come on, why are you
suddenly asking for dinner?

385
00:23:39,660 --> 00:23:40,890
Ask Dad to treat you.

386
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:44,290
Is a dinner from your dad the same
as a dinner from my son?

387
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:48,030
A husband and a son are never the same.

388
00:23:48,570 --> 00:23:51,100
I want my son to treat me, you hear?

389
00:23:52,340 --> 00:23:53,370
What would you like to eat?

390
00:23:53,940 --> 00:23:55,010
Order whatever you want.

391
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:57,370
Just don't blame me later
when you gain weight.

392
00:24:02,680 --> 00:24:05,420
Aren't you Lawyer Kang Baek Ho?

393
00:24:05,850 --> 00:24:10,050
Look who it is!
It's Ms. Jin Hong Ju, isn't it?

394
00:24:10,420 --> 00:24:11,450
Hello.

395
00:24:12,790 --> 00:24:14,490
What brings you here?

396
00:24:15,690 --> 00:24:17,060
I got stood up.

397
00:24:17,590 --> 00:24:19,460
I had plans with some friends
from my college reunion,

398
00:24:20,060 --> 00:24:23,930
- but it turns out I got the date wrong.
- Oh, dear.

399
00:24:24,630 --> 00:24:27,000
Then you weren't really stood up,
were you?

400
00:24:29,140 --> 00:24:33,410
Have a seat. This is perfect.
You can have dinner with us.

401
00:24:33,740 --> 00:24:35,510
Are you sure?

402
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:38,550
Baek Ho, you don't mind
if I join you, do you?

403
00:24:39,950 --> 00:24:41,620
Yes, please do.

404
00:24:46,620 --> 00:24:47,620
Oh my.

405
00:24:48,830 --> 00:24:50,330
My goodness...

406
00:24:50,630 --> 00:24:54,700
You two look so good together,
sitting side-by-side like that.

407
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:57,100
Mom, how can you say something
so embarrassing?

408
00:24:57,730 --> 00:24:59,270
I don't mind. I like the sound of it.

409
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:04,570
See? She's so sweet and cheerful.

410
00:25:06,380 --> 00:25:09,780
Hong Ju, I bet you have
men lining up for you.

411
00:25:10,310 --> 00:25:14,220
You're pretty, have a great personality,
a stable job,

412
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:18,320
and on top of that, you're the daughter
of Dream Group's Chairman Ma!

413
00:25:18,620 --> 00:25:21,490
Wow, on top of everything,
your family is powerful too.

414
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:24,290
Oh my, you're a total catch!
Truly the best.

415
00:25:25,930 --> 00:25:29,870
- You're making me blush, Mother.
- Excuse me, I think I'll get going.

416
00:25:29,930 --> 00:25:33,670
Hey! You said you were treating me.
Where are your manners?

417
00:25:33,770 --> 00:25:35,640
Mom, let's have dinner some other time.

418
00:25:36,110 --> 00:25:37,810
Tonight, I'd like to be
alone with Hong Ju.

419
00:25:40,910 --> 00:25:41,980
With me?

420
00:25:43,410 --> 00:25:44,450
Fine.

421
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:47,620
You young people want to be alone,
is that it?

422
00:25:48,420 --> 00:25:50,220
Then this old mom will get
out of your hair.

423
00:26:01,870 --> 00:26:02,870
Hong Ju.

424
00:26:06,170 --> 00:26:07,270
Yes, Baek Ho?

425
00:26:15,050 --> 00:26:16,410
Where could Chae Hwa Young have gone?

426
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:18,780
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

427
00:26:26,020 --> 00:26:28,460
(1:10 p.m., Director Ma Seo Rin)

428
00:26:29,630 --> 00:26:30,630
Don't tell me...

429
00:26:31,490 --> 00:26:32,800
Did she suspect me?

430
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:42,270
What about Seo Rin?

431
00:26:43,140 --> 00:26:45,410
She was in a meeting with
General Manager Kang until a moment ago.

432
00:26:45,710 --> 00:26:46,710
I see.

433
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:50,810
I'll know soon enough. I just have to go
and check on Oh Jang Mi.

434
00:26:51,450 --> 00:26:53,920
- I'm going on ahead.
- Yes, ma'am.

435
00:28:00,820 --> 00:28:02,890
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

436
00:28:22,270 --> 00:28:23,970
(The First Man)

437
00:28:24,040 --> 00:28:25,240
Looks like this is for you.

438
00:28:25,780 --> 00:28:27,840
What is it? "Kang Nam Bong."

439
00:28:27,940 --> 00:28:31,920
"Next time, I'll send this to your wife,
Lawyer Han Young Ja."

440
00:28:31,950 --> 00:28:33,550
You seem to be in a good mood,
Team Leader Jin.

441
00:28:33,680 --> 00:28:35,420
Because my love life is going very well.

442
00:28:35,750 --> 00:28:39,360
- Who's the lucky guy?
- How about a double date with Seo Rin?

443
00:28:39,660 --> 00:28:43,590
The launch of the new high-end watch brand
absolutely has to be at our hotel.

444
00:28:43,790 --> 00:28:47,000
Chae Hwa Young, I'm going to
tear you down, piece by piece.

445
00:28:49,330 --> 00:28:51,330
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
